Description: Ostracon, small fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is light-brown in section, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and remains of one line of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393970) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393970)
